Modifications made in this derivative (Roster), relative to ADE, include,
but are not limited to:

  - Renamed the product to Roster.
  - Removed the hosted cloud, authentication, Electric SQL sync, and
    OpenRouter/bring-your-own-key integrations.
  - Reduced the agent runtimes to Claude Code and Codex only, and replaced
    the provider model bar with a per-runtime model-variant picker.
  - Introduced guarded-by-default agent permission modes (native CLI
    approvals/sandbox), with an explicit opt-in for full autonomy.
  - Replaced the in-app terminal engine with ghostty-web (Ghostty's
    terminal core, WASM), with the xterm.js engine retained as a fallback,
    and added an "Open in Ghostty" external-launch action.
  - Hardened the Hermes-style persistent agent memory: agent-authored
    skills are loaded back into sessions, the write-back protocol is
    imported on Claude Code, the user profile is shared across agents, and
    the reflection stop-hook gained trivial-session skipping, a
    concurrency lock, and memory size-budget enforcement.
  - Security hardening: authenticated the local hook/notification server,
    removed all telemetry (PostHog/Sentry), tightened the Content Security
    Policy and Electron webPreferences, gated the CDP remote-debugging
    port, validated git clone URLs, and added a workspace-trust gate for
    repository-supplied setup commands.

ADE's own modifications relative to Superset are recorded in that project.
